Ah, well to do what you're trying to do I would suggest something more like
```{% for auteur in dynamic_page_hubdb_row.auteurs %}
  {% if auteur.name == 'Joanie Fontaine' %}
    Joanie's bio goes here
  {% elif auter.name == 'Estelle Filiatrault-Begin' %}
    Estelle's bio goes here
  {% elif auter.name == 'And so on' %}
    And so forth
  {% endif %}
{% endfor %}```

Or even better, turn `auteurs` into a foreign ID column and store the metadata for them in another HubDB table. Then you just do something like this:
```{% for auteur in dynamic_page_hubdb_row.auteurs %}
  &lt;div gr-grid="row" class="author"&gt;
    &lt;div gr-grid="sm-3"&gt;
        &lt;div class="author__picture"&gt;                         
            &lt;img src="{{ auteur.portrait.url|escape }}" alt="{{ auteur.name|escape }}"&gt;                          
        &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div gr-grid="sm-9"&gt;
        &lt;h2 class="h2 author__title"&gt;
            &lt;strong&gt;{{ auteur.name }}&lt;/strong&gt;
            &lt;br/&gt;{{ auteur.title }}
        &lt;/h2&gt;
        &lt;div class="typography author__description"&gt;
            {{ auteur.description }}
        &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
{% endfor %}```
No need to update the template whenever you want to change one of these people or add a new one or whatever
